    <briefdescription>
<para>Command that applies 2D directional movement to a GameObject. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This command encapsulates a movement request consisting of a normalized direction vector and a speed factor derived from analog stick magnitude. When executed, it invokes Move2DComponent::move() to update rotation target and movement speed.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The target GameObject must have a Move2DComponent attached for this command to have any effect.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para>helios::engine::runtime::messaging::command::Command </para>
